<plot>This Traveltalk visit to India spends the first half in the port city of Bombay, where we see the famous "hanging gardens." We then watch a horse race at Bombay's race track. The spectators seem more interested in their outfits than in the horses. Then it's off to Delhi, with its many temples, and New Delhi, where the British influence is still seen in the dress and demeanor of the Indian military troops. The last two minutes are spent in Agra, site of the beautiful Taj Mahal shrine.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?318841</url></doc>
